%description:
Regression test for RFC 3032 penultimate hop popping (PHP) in examples/mpls/ldp
(network LDPTEST), default configuration (advertiseImplicitNull = true).

Only host1 sends (host3/host4 are silent -- both are UdpSink -- so the only
live LSP in the whole simulation is host1->host2, over LSR1 -> LSR2 -> LSR3).
This makes every "doStackOps: {POP}" line in the log unambiguously about this
one flow: LDP control-plane traffic between adjacent peers is never
label-switched (Ldp::lookupLabel explicitly excludes LDP's own TCP/UDP
traffic), so with PHP enabled the FIRST pop for this FEC can only be LSR3
(the actual egress, connected to host2) advertising the implicit null label
and LSR2 (the penultimate LSR) popping instead of swapping.

mpls_php.test (this file) and mpls_php_disabled.test (advertiseImplicitNull =
false) run the identical scenario; mpls_php_disabled.test is the negative case
that locks in the pre-PHP egress-allocates-a-real-pop-label behavior.

Wording note: with the DU/independent/liberal defaults (RFC-conventional label
distribution, see Ldp.ned's distributionMode/controlMode/retentionMode), the
egress advertisement is now proactively sent via Ldp::duAdvertiseToPeer rather
than in reactive response to a Label Request (Ldp::processLABEL_REQUEST) --
the assertion below matches the new (DU) EV_INFO wording; the underlying PHP
outcome (implicit null label 3 advertised, LSR2 pops) is unchanged.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.ldp.LDPTEST
sim-time-limit = 2s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "info"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-#${runnumber}.sca"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host2"

**.host{2..4}.numApps = 1
**.host{2..4}.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host{2..4}.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host4.rt"

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR5.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

**.LSR*.holdTime = 6s
**.LSR*.helloInterval = 2s

**.scenarioManager.script = xml("<scenario/>")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the data plane is label-switched, as usual (ingress LSR1 still pushes)
%contains: stdout
doStackOps: {PUSH
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# LSR3, egress for host2's FEC, advertises the implicit null label instead of
%# allocating a real pop entry
%contains: stdout
DU: advertising unsolicited Label Mapping (egress) label=3 for fec addr=10.0.2.1
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# LSR2, the penultimate hop, therefore pops the label itself rather than
%# swapping it -- with only this one live flow in the whole simulation, any
%# POP in the log can only be this one
%contains: stdout
doStackOps: {POP}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# host traffic is still delivered end-to-end despite the label being popped
%# one hop earlier than before
%postrun-command: grep "packetReceived:count" results/General-#0.sca | awk '$NF > 0 { print "DELIVERED", $0 }' > delivered.out
%contains: delivered.out
DELIVERED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
